cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with stereo depth estimation in robotics, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes an end-to-end learned approach for disparity prediction, which involves training a model using machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational constraints of the problem, which is a common issue in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
